On the remote sensor:

0. install full raspberry pi os configuration.  
1. enable camera via raspi-config.
2. apt-get update ; apt-get upgrade -y; apt-get dist-upgrade -y
3. sudo apt-get install sense-hat build-essential git
4. sudo apt-get install python3-picamera
5. sudo apt-get install gpsd gpsd-clients python-gps
6. wget https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py
7. sudo python3 get-pip.py
8. sudo pip install gpsd-py3
9. git clone https://github.com/japharl/kapcode.git
10. sudo chmod -R 777 /home/pi/kapcode/*
11. sudo chown -R pi:pi /home/pi/kapcode/*
12. sudo chmod 777 /etc/rc.local
13. sudo apt-get install cpanminus
15. sudo cpanm Proc::Background File::Path File::Slurper
16. sudo vi /etc/rc.local
# Add line:
nohup bash -x /home/pi/kapcode/init.sh &

On the local GCS: 
(NOTE - this pi zero has a pi oled (from adafruit) and the pi has a lblink wifi adapter.) 

0. install minimal raspberry pi raspbian configuration.
0a. Don't install peripherals to the pi until prompted. :)
1. sudo raspi-config 
1a. connect your local access point via primary wifi access point on board.
1b.  enable i2c / ssh (optional)
1c. sudo shutdown -h now
1d. sudo reboot
1. apt-get update ; apt-get upgrade -y ; apt-get dist-upgrade -y
2. apt-get install build-essential git build-essential python-dev python-pip
4. sudo pip-install RPi.GPIO
5. install python-imaging python-smbus
6. git clone https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_Python_SSD1306.git
7. sudo python setup.py install
8. sudo i2cdetect -y 1 # Verify 3c is installed.
9. sudo apt-get install -y dnsmasq hostapd # Configure wlan1 and wlan0 
